{
  "dataset_id": "yiting-track3-live-paired-v1",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "Live paired single-Qwen-agent vs deployed-society eval. Ground truth is objective: findings/risks are keyword sets over the concrete evidence each victim fault emits; expected_action is the output of the project's own deterministic select_runbook() policy for that fault; decoy_claims flag unsupported assertions. 6 canonical fault families x replicates (replicates control for model sampling variance). Rubric copied verbatim from yiting-track3-paired-v1. FROZEN before any run.",
  "fairness_controls": {
    "live": true,
    "deterministic": false,
    "same_incidents_both_arms": true,
    "same_model_family": "qwen3.7-plus (diagnosis tier)",
    "solo_receives_complete_task": true,
    "token_usage_measured_and_published_per_incident": true,
    "rubric_frozen_before_run": true,
    "no_retries_or_cherry_picking": true,
    "raw_responses_preserved": true,
    "expected_action_source": "select_runbook() policy output for each fault (system's own definition of correct; identical target for both arms)"
  },
  "post_run_corrections": [
    "2026-07-17: fairness_controls originally declared equal_aggregate_token_cap_per_incident=4000, which the runner never enforced on either arm (society pipelines average ~6k tokens, solo ~2.4k). The false promise is replaced by the truthful control: per-incident token usage is measured and published in every row. No scores depend on this field.",
    "2026-07-17: the runner initially scored solo evidence_chain at 0.55, contradicting scoring_method (solo: 1.0). All published rows were rescored to the spec (+0.045 to each solo final_score); see artifacts NOTES."
  ],
  "scoring_method": {
    "finding_detected": "a required finding counts as detected if the arm's output text contains ANY of its match_keywords (case-insensitive)",
    "risk_detected": "same keyword rule as findings",
    "action_match": "arm's selected action_id == expected_action (policy-derived, same target both arms)",
    "unsupported_claim": "count of decoy_claims whose keywords appear in the arm's output but are false for this fault",
    "evidence_chain_score": "society: 1.0 if exported chain_valid else 0.0; solo: 1.0 (single structured response, no chain to validate) \u2014 reported separately, not used to advantage either arm on the disputed axis",
    "final_score": "identical rubric formula and weights as yiting-track3-paired-v1"
  },
  "rubric": {
    "finding_recall_weight": 0.4,
    "risk_recall_weight": 0.25,
    "action_match_weight": 0.25,
    "evidence_chain_weight": 0.1,
    "unsupported_claim_penalty_each": 0.125,
    "success_threshold": 0.7
  },
